('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DIPLO_3_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_9', 'War of Liberation: You can declare war of liberation if a friend or ally defeats their city, and if you have done civic research in the diplomatic service. You must deny your purpose and also wait for 5 before declaring war. There are no special requirements to deactivate your account. You will experience the heat of the moment just like a formal war if you attack another enemy city, and if you hit a hostile city, you will experience 600% of the heat of the moment! This is the most expensive punishment for diplomacy and warming, because cities burned in the name of freedom are particularly bad for other civilizations in the world.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DIPLO_3_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_10', 'Colonial War: You could declare a colonial war against the civilization behind you with 2 technologies, that you have researched civic nationalism. You must deny your purpose and also wait for 5 before declaring war. This Casus Belli had only 50% of the heating penalty at the time of the declaration of war and captured cities. If you activate a city, you will receive the full and warm punishment as an official battle for time, since the world will no longer buy your excuse to "bring the light" to your goal.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DIPLO_3_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_11', 'Civil War: You can declare a civil war against civilization if you have researched civilization. The goal must be 2 cities in 10 tiles in 2 in your city. You must drop your goals and wait for 5 as well. Casus Belli reduced the penalty for the official war at the time by 25% to declare war and capture cities. Urban growth carries a penalty of 50% of the heated punishment of a formal war. Casus Belli This is an advantage if you want to eliminate hostile cities in the regions where you want to expand.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DIPLO_3_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_12', 'Battle for the Golden Age: You can declare war for the Golden Age if you choose the weapon! Dedication, and unlock your goals. You don''t have to wait until you try to get your license.You have failed to attend until then, the city''s heating and seizure penalties are only 25% of the heating penalty at this time, making it one of the least diplomatic means of seizing the opposite country. Heating penalties imposed on a city are equivalent to a warmer official -300% of typical heating penalties at this time. Being a golden - age does make you respectful of other nations, but it does not allow you to practice impunity.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DIPLO_3_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_13', 'Reward War: You may have declared a revenge war if you have investigated the civilization of the Old Kingdom, another civilization has violated the promises made to you in the last 30 rounds. You must deny your purpose and also wait for 5 before declaring war. During the rewards wars you have a 50% reduction in the formal war penalty at the time of declaring war and capturing cities, but the falling cities will give you a 200% penalty at the time of the hottest penalty. Even if the enemy does not keep his promise to you, you do not have the right to retaliate against those cities.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DIPLO_3_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_14', 'Conceptual Warfare: You could declare conceptual warfare if you research civic concepts, and you have a Level 3 state that is different from your goals. You must drop your goals and wait for 5 as well. During the conceptual war you have a 50% reduction in the warm-up penalty period for declaring war, capturing cities, and towns.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_T_ROOSEVELT_CHAPTER_DETAILED_BODY', 'At the beginning of the game, the only American advantage is +5 [icon_force] fighting force in their home continent. They want to expand their continent quickly and move to get support in nearby cities. With their diplomatic political position turning to savages, their choice of government is important, although the Common Republic and the Trade Republic are the most profitable in the United States. They should also consider building a national history museum in place of their government. With its movie studio, National Park Bonus, and two unique post-industrial cells, it shines from the 20th century.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_COMBAT_11_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'Proclaiming war against another civilization will give you penalties for dealing with another civilization in the game, known as the Hot Penalty. This reflects a lack of confidence in other leaders or fear of your own actions. The most common way to declare war, and the most common way to calculate all wars, including punishment, is formal warfare. In this case, the civilization first indicates a target civilization and then declares an official war.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_COMBAT_11_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'The penalty is increasing, as war becomes an unacceptable solution to the conflicts between the civilizations of the world. These situations also include those you have been in. In most cases, declaring war and capturing an enemy city will give you the hottest punishment of the moment, and beating a city will give you three times the hottest punishment of the moment. Some casus belli (see casus belli section under diplomacy) may change their punishment, reduce certain actions, or make them more expensive. Other measures, such as the use of nuclear weapons, will also make a difference in your punishment.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_COMBAT_13_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'To complete a district take 3 movement points, or your entire movement. Each district building must be relied upon individually, and granted a district-based shop type. See Secretary''s main article once injected, a building can no longer be injected until it has been returned online to the owner (via a manufacturing menu and takes 25% of the value of that building''s initial construction output.)'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_SCIENCE_2_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'Science comes from a variety of sources, including your own [icon_citizen] (0.5 instead of [icon_citizen]), your own castle, some politics, some religious beliefs, some resources, miracles, business, and of course the campus district and its residents. Take a look at Civilopedia for a science source [icon_Science].'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGEGROUP_EXPANSION_NAME', 'The Promotion and Promotion'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_PRIDE_MOMENTS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'Historical Records'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_PRIDE_MOMENTS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'Historical moments are important events that occur throughout the history of the game, from being the first to choosing a new form of government, to the establishment of a special unit, to the discovery of natural miracles. There are dozens of historical moments during the game, representing the world''s first victory with the player. The time will change according to the time.The times will change over time. For example, the cleanliness of barbarian camps in the Middle Ages is a milestone, but the cleanliness of a modern - day camp will not even qualify for recognition. You can view your date at any time while playing by clicking on the date calendar in the toolbar at the top left. [newline][newline] Any historical moment added to bridge when you come out of that moment on, which is the limit of whether you will rise to the golden age or sink into the next dark age. If you have several historical periods at once, it means that you are likely to enter the Golden Age in the following periods. If you are the first player in the world to get a certain amount of time in history, you will earn a lot of epoch points.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOLDEN_AGES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'The Golden Age and the Darkness'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOLDEN_AGES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'As the game continues from the age of civilization you can enter the Golden Age or the Dark Age. If you are better than other civilizations or have completed many historical periods, then there is a good chance that you will enter the Golden Age in the next period. If you start falling behind, you may find yourself in the dark ages. [newline]Gold is a time of great prosperity for your people. Your loyalty will fall to a lower level than normal. Not only will your cities be more likely to remain in your civilization, but you may even become the nearest city to your civilization. Then you can choose the option for next time. Devotions are powerful tools that protect a specific part of your civilization. But know that earning the golden age is difficult to earn the next golden age, and it is easy to fall into the black age. Your loyalty decreases faster than normal, which can lead to cities on the outskirts of your civilization leaving and becoming independent cities, or beating other players and joining their civilization. You can help prevent this by using your admins [icon_governor], or strategically choosing to lose their city (which you can expect to restore later.)Don''t despair or get upset if you find yourself in a dark time because you have a chance to enter the brave era. Your limits for entering the Golden Age will decrease if you are in the Dark Age, and if you cross the limits of the Golden Age, you will enter the Brave Age. The hero''s parents will allow you to choose from three devotions for next season! This can really put you ahead of the player in the Golden Age of the Golden Age, if you could make the most of your talent.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOLDEN_AGES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'If you are above the black age, but do not have enough high scores to enter the Golden Age, you enter the usual age. During the normal age you can still opt for dedication at this age, but you will not receive any other bonuses or penalties.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOLDEN_AGES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'Dark times also give you access to special dark times policies. Wild card policies can give you options to get out of the dark ages, but they can be expensive. For example, the isolation policy provides bonuses for domestic business routes [icon_TradeRoute], but it prevents you from building or buying settlements or setting up new cities.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOLDEN_AGES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'You may have to complete deductions during the ordinary and dark ages to increase your period scores, which gives you the perfect opportunity to earn a future golden age.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_LOYALTY_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'The sincerity'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_LOYALTY_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'Honesty is the measure of a city devoted to its civilization. Each city has a loyalty value of 0 to 100, which reflects how many citizens [icon_citizen] in the city want to remain as part of your civilization. When loyalty decreases to 75, city productivity and growth are penalized by 25%. When loyalty decreases to 25, city productivity is penalized by 50% growth and punished by 75%. When loyalty reaches 0, the city rises up against the landlord and becomes a free city. Free cities are uncivilized and are trying to defend themselves against military intervention. If the loyalty of the Free City falls to 0, its independence attempt fails, and they are seeking to enter civilization. Which civilization is asked to join depends on who imposes most of the pressure on the free city during their independence. In this way, a free city can safely bring into your civilization (or well into your civilization).'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_LOYALTY_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'Integrity changes each cycle based on many factors, but the most important is the pressure of the citizen [icon_citizen] living in or near the city. If [icon_city] pressures are higher than those of other civilizations, the integrity of the city will increase (up to +20 per second). If the other pressures of civilization are strong, the integrity of the city will decrease (up to -20 per turn). Each citizen (icon_citizen) performs a baseline pressure of 1, but it can be reversed. For example, [icon_city] citizens living in a capital are still under pressure 1. The golden and brave age adds 0.5 to all citizens [icon_citizen], while the black age brings it down to 0.5. This pressure [icon_citizen] has an impact on cities in 9 drawers, but it is 10% less effective than a remote part.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_LOYALTY_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'The percentage of [icon_governor] in city and happiness is another strong factor that affects the integrity of the city per cycle. In addition, cities that have been defeated by military forces will be punished for loyalty, but this can be reduced by maintaining an armored military unit in the city. Use loyalty glasses to identify loyalty issues, including sources of pressure in nearby cities. A full description of the factors affecting the integrity of the city can be found in the Integrity and City Board Governor section.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_LOYALTY_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'For players who have established a religion, cities get +3 honesty to follow that religion, but -3 honesty to each turn if they follow the religion of another player.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'Administrators'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'Administrators allow players to manage the cities of civilization in the following ways: [newline] [icon_bullet] Appoint administrators with special powers and authority to serve civilizations.[edit] [edit] [Newline][icon_bullet] The assignments of governors to a particular city to civilization are named.Use administrators assigned to a specific jurisdiction to have different and specific effects in that city.[Newline] [icon_bullet] Use delegate administrations to increase the process of building strong loyalty to the city.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'There are 7 different governors who can be listed and advertised: [icon_cult] ''[icon_cult]'' [icon_cult] ''[icon_cult]'' [icon_cult] '''' [newline]   ''icon_cult]'' ''[icon_cult]'' [icon_cult] '''' [icon_cult] ''''.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'Appointment of a President: [new line] Administrators and promotions obtained through the use of the President''s address. The Governor''s name was opened throughout the game, mainly by the civic tree, but also by the construction of the State Plaza and its buildings, and the construction of the Casa de Contratación Wonder. Once the counselor is appointed, they may be assigned to a city to carry out their duties. Players can have one ruler of any kind of civilization, and can assign one ruler to a city at a time.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'Ride the President: [new line]Players can also use the president''s address to encourage administrators who have already been nominated for them. Each type of beard has a unique rose tree. The incentive option opens up new powers that the governor may exercise when building in the city to which they are assigned.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_5', 'There are several ways that managers can influence a city for which they are responsible: [newline] [icon_bullet] recognizes the city''s access to civilizations, thereby increasing the loyalty of its citizens [icon_citizen].[Newline] [icon_bullet] Apply for special powers of this city governor when he is established there.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_6', 'President Farmajo''s first call to transfer power at,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,, this time means the time it will take for the governor to create policies and laws, propose changes, and build power and influence in this city. The amount of time “exceeds” depends on the president. Once a particular governor has stood in a city and left the city, the appointed time will begin to fall apart. After the required time, the governor''s special power comes into effect. This includes their heart skills, as well as any promotions given to them. This ability is random, because there is no need to activate the player, and it is not a one-time use effect.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_GOVERNORS_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_7', 'Presidential Determination Changes:[offline]Sometimes during the game it is necessary to change the location of your administrators. Managers can move to another city at any time, but remember that once assigned to another city it will take time to set up there. If a counselor is assigned to a city that already has a counselor, the current counselor will be removed from the city and taken back to your counselor''s bar, ready to be assigned to a new location.[Newline][Newline] Administrators may be assigned to a single city in their civilization except one. The ''diplomat'' chair is unique and can be assigned to the city area as well as to any city in its civilization. “Diplomacy” cannot be assigned to a city-state and the player is currently struggling.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ALLIANCES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'On the other hand, all'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_ALLIANCES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'A bond is a relationship between two different civilizations, a mutual agreement that sometimes works together. To enter the Alliance, you must first declare Friend of Civilization, and both civilizations must have been surveyed by civil society.[newline] [newline] [newline]There are different types of Covenants, each offering different benefits to each other according to its type. The effects of these levels are cumulative, so if you are in a Level 3 alliance, you also get Level 1 and Level 2 effects. When you are in a coalition with another player, you get coalition points for each round.  Organizations that avoid increasing your level of coalition, resulting in more benefits in your coalition.  You can increase the rate at which you can earn coalition points in trade with your allies. Each bond, regardless of its type, provides for open borders and treats mutual defense. Members of the Coalition cannot declare war against each other.You may have one type of bond with another civilization, and once you create this bond, you may not have another civilization, even if you may have another type of bond. For example, you may have a research alliance with Korea, so you cannot set up a new research alliance with Korea. However, you can create a military, cultural, religious or economic link with Cree. Note that this limits the 5 total alliances in the game.[newline][newline] research alliance [icon_bull] level 1: [icon_trade route] trade routes between allies provides more science [icon_science]. Level 3: It provides a bonus science when you learn a technology similar to your allies or one that your allies have completed, and where your allies are investigating a technology that you have completed.[newline] [newline] Culture Alliance [icon_bull] Level 1: The alliance does not exert any loyalty pressure, and [icon_trade route] trade routes between allies provide more culture [icon_culture]. [new ico