('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_EMERGENCY_ALLIANCES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'In the event of an emergency'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_EMERGENCY_ALLIANCES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'Emergencies are triggered in response to a serious act by a civilization, such as the conjunction of a city state, the transformation of the Holy Spirit, or the launch of a nuclear attack. Other game civilizations will have the opportunity to join the player who triggered the rescue. Civilization declares that friends or allies with targeted civilizations are only invited to join the infidelity emergency.[Newline][Newline] Joining citizens will work towards a specific goal that should be achieved within a limited time. It can also be helpful for team members to help them stay on target. If the goal is completed, all members who participated in the rescue will receive a special prize with an expensive gold [icon_gold], but if the time limit expires first, there will be a fixed penalty and the goal will receive gold [icon_gold], instead.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_EMERGENCY_ALLIANCES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'These are the emergency situations in the game:[newline] [icon_bullet] Military emergency: A civilization that led to some kind of victory has now taken over another civilized city.  Members are required to maintain the target in the city. Members receive a bonus movement [icon_movement] on the target territory, and have peace, open borders, and a shared view of each other.  All members will be at war with the goal and the strength of the goal [icon_boost] will decrease when they fight. If they do, they will get a bonus recovery in the target territory in the future. If a member can''t catch enough cities by the quick end, then Target wins and receives a regular bonus on their [icon_string] city strength. State of the city: Civilization took more than and surpassed city government. The city''s local government should release members. All members will be at war with the goal and will have peace, open borders, and shared visions with each other. If they are aware of it, then they are aware of it. If the target retains control of the city area, then it wins, and receives a bonus of [icon_gold] gold per turn for each of the trade routes [icon_TradeRoute]. Immediate Religion: An act of religious propaganda transformed civilization into a holy city. Members are required to leave the holy city of their new religion in order to convert a certain number of them before the rush is over. If he wins, each player receives a medal. Target success if members are unable to avoid the new religion by appropriate number of iterations before the end of the emergency. Then there will be a lot of pressure on the new religion.[edit] Conservatives in the United States are forced to keep the goal in their cities. Members receive a bonus movement [icon_movement] on the target territory, and have peace, open borders, and a shared view of each other.  All members will be at war with the goal and the strength of the goal [icon_boost] will decrease when they fight. If the member wins, then the target military units face an even greater punishment and more permanent [icon_force] force when fighting the member. If they fail, all member cities will experience a decline in loyalty. [Newline] [icon_bullet] Quick: Civilization declares war against another civilization, with a hierarchical bond. Members are required to maintain the target in the city. Members receive a bonus movement [icon_movement] on the target territory, and have peace, open borders, and a shared view of each other.  All members will be at war with the goal and strength of the goal [icon_boost] will be diminished when they fight. [icon_TradeRoute] Trade routes between members and goals are canceled, and [icon_TradeRoute] trade routes between members also provide [icon_product] products. If the member wins, then the target military units will face constant [icon_force] punishment for forces opposing the member. If the member is unable to take enough cities by the quick end, then the target wins and earns a constant drop in war alerts when it fights against the member.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_EMERGENCY_ALLIANCES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'The ability of civilization to participate in emergencies is determined by its diplomatic relations with other civilizations and other cities in the game.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_FREE_CITIES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'The free cities'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_FREE_CITIES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'A free city is a city that has lost its original civilization due to loss of integrity. These are not city-states, as they are probably looking forward to joining one of the largest civilizations in the game. The free city has the integrity to protect it as a normal city, and it accepts the integrity pressures of other civilizations. If his integrity reaches 0, he will join the civilization that has imposed the greatest pressure on integrity since the free city became independent. This means that there is a competition against other civilizations when you are looking to attract a free city to your civilization. Increasing your loyalty will increase your chances of gaining more loyalty in the city.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_FREE_CITIES_1_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'The Free City will improve the correction of needles and sponge cells to protect itself, and it can build walls to protect itself. If a civilization is attacked, the free city will try to retreat from one of the civilized cities. Otherwise, citizens will follow suit, looking forward to seeing the most interesting civilizations in the world for themselves.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE', 'The Decepticons'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'Deductions are a way to focus on the growth of your civilization at the beginning of each era, from the common time. A list of devotions available at the beginning of the epochal changes during the game, and you can find some devotions across multiple epochs. During the Black Age, dedication is a reliable way to increase your seasonal score when working in the brave age. When you enter the Golden Age, their dedication becomes more powerful, no longer providing epoch points, but now offers a great bonus for your civilization.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_2', 'Bread, brushes, and voice: Win +1 Era score every time you activate [icon_CivicBoosted] promotion. +1 Era of points for the construction of a building with a large working place. If selected at the beginning of the Golden Age, the incentive [icon_CivicBoosted] provides an additional 10% of civilian costs. Each city receives +1 [icon_Culture] culture in each specialized district.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_3', 'Payment Reform: Get +1 Era score every time you successfully complete [icon_TradeRoute] trading path.  If you are chosen at the beginning of the golden age, you cannot be plundered. International trade routes [icon_TradeRoute] offer +3 [icon_Gold] gold per specialty unit in a foreign city.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_4', 'Hic Sunt Dracones: Win +3 era scores every time you find a new continent or natural wonder. Win +1 IRA scores every time you kill a non-combat unit in the Barbary Navy. If selected at the beginning of the Golden Age, +3 of the urban population lived on a different continent than in your first city. [edit] Attraction and attraction +2 Integration of revolution in non-existent cities [icon_capital] in the capital region.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_5', 'Heart Race: There are +2 era points for any industrial building built on or after. If selected at the beginning of the Golden Age, +10% [icon_output] output is oriented to the industrial age with signs later. The Municipal Campus [icon_science] also offers scientific adhesion production [icon_product].'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_6', 'Note: Get +1 era points every time you build a new special district. If selected at the beginning of the Golden Age, +2 [motion icon] movement of all buildings. You may be able to buy them with confidence. Buyers and sellers are 30% cheaper to buy [icon_faith] faith and gold.'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_7', 'For Arms!: Win +1 Era scores every time you kill an unarmed soldier in war and +2 Era scores every time you kill an unarmed soldier in war. If selected at the beginning of the Golden Age, it opens a special casus belli that provides 75% less fine than heating in a formal action and can be used immediately after targeting down. [edit] [edit] Speech about language use]'),
('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DEDICATIONS_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_8', 'Evangelical exodus: There are +2 era scores every time you turn a city to your core religion for the first time. If selected at the beginning of the Golden Age, +2 [icon_movement] movements of all the apostles, ambassadors, and investigators. In addition, newly-trained people receive +2 charges. +4 [icon_GreatProphet] Points of the Great Prophet instead of overturning them.'),
