('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_DIPLO_11_CHAPTER_CONTENT_PARA_1', 'The defense agreement is an agreement between two leaders to come help each other by targeting the declaration of war. If a member of the defensive league is targeted, another member will also declare war against the attacker. If the two leaders are in a coalition, they will automatically have a defense agreement between them. These packages are no longer available because they are linear elements of diplomatic agreements.'),
