('en_US', 'LOC_PEDIA_UNITS_PAGE_UNIT_MISSIONARY_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'A missionary is someone who feels called to spread his faith and convert unbelievers. This process is called proselytizing, and it can be accompanied by works of charity on behalf of future believers or by more powerful means. Deacons may have been anointed ones, such as priests, or faithful servants of faith. Operators sometimes provide a glimpse of their pre-realized civilization, including recordings of beliefs, customs, and languages, although often with the intention of changing these into their preferred beliefs.'),
